1
00:01:37,850 --> 00:01:41,000
[The Epoch of Miyu]

2
00:01:41,070 --> 00:01:43,979
[Episode 29]

3
00:01:47,229 --> 00:01:49,289
My son's hearing aid is custom-made.

4
00:01:49,789 --> 00:01:51,640
You just say you
could not find it and that is it?

5
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,580
What am I supposed to do?

6
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:53,759
For tomorrow's
foreign language listening test,

7
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:54,590
what is my son going to do?

8
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:56,120
Ma'am, please calm down first.

9
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,580
What is the point of giving me water?

10
00:01:57,580 --> 00:01:59,580
What I want is my son's hearing aid.

11
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,620
Ma'am, please calm down.

12
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:04,630
I will help you solve
any problems you have.

13
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:07,830
Hello.

14
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:09,310
Do you remember

15
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:11,850
when the last time
you took off your hearing aid was?

16
00:02:11,850 --> 00:02:13,400
Why are you questioning him?

17
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,950
He's just a child.
He doesn't remember a thing!

18
00:02:14,950 --> 00:02:16,400
If you twist him with a few words,

19
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,910
it'll be easier for you
to deny it later, right?

20
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:18,870
I'm telling you,

21
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,220
the hearing aid was lost
in your hotel room.

22
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:21,910
That forewoman of yours

23
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:23,470
can't escape responsibility!

24
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:24,829
Ma'am, please don't worry.

25
00:02:24,829 --> 00:02:26,280
I will go to the executive floor right now

26
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,520
to look into the situation.

27
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,030
Please wait here for a moment.

28
00:02:29,030 --> 00:02:30,190
I'll be right back.

29
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:46,090
Miyu.

30
00:02:46,790 --> 00:02:47,510
Did you find it?

31
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:48,190
No.

32
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:50,079
I searched the room,

33
00:02:50,110 --> 00:02:52,030
checked all the corners in the hallway,

34
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,940
and even took apart the toilet.

35
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,210
Now we are going through the trash,

36
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,770
but still haven't found it.

37
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:00,700
When did they come back?

38
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:03,780
I know. The parents came back first,

39
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:04,920
and then the kid

40
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:06,540
came back half an hour later.

41
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,110
When the kid came back,

42
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:09,770
did he have his hearing aid on?

43
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,280
Was he wearing it?

44
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,290
I didn't notice.

45
00:03:13,770 --> 00:03:16,630
The kid must have gone
somewhere else along the way.

46
00:03:16,690 --> 00:03:18,360
You need to clean this up quickly.

47
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,690
The garbage truck is waiting downstairs.

48
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:22,570
Today is garbage collection day.

49
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:23,650
What should we do?

50
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,010
What should we do, Miyu?

51
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,840
Ma'am, could you ask the head of logistics

52
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,430
to have

53
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:30,940
the garbage truck wait a bit longer?

54
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:31,590
Thank you.

55
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,680
Hurry up.

56
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:34,190
Okay, thanks.

57
00:03:40,430 --> 00:03:41,740
Mr. Ji is here.

58
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:45,020
Don't panic.

59
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,740
It's not that serious.

60
00:03:54,410 --> 00:03:56,130
Calm the guests down first.

61
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,020
Leave the rest to me.

62
00:03:58,079 --> 00:03:58,870
Yes, Mr. Ji.

63
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:04,000
I'll go ask the child again.

64
00:04:04,290 --> 00:04:05,130
Wait for me.

65
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:06,960
Thanks, Miyu.

66
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,160
-Let’s keep looking.
-Yes.

67
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,550
[Camera 01]

68
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:20,910
Pause it.

69
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,290
Zoom in on this footage.

70
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:25,800
Okay.

71
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:28,830
Focus on the ear.

72
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:29,800
Yes.

73
00:04:36,270 --> 00:04:37,470
Show me the elevator footage

74
00:04:37,470 --> 00:04:38,490
from that same time.

75
00:04:38,490 --> 00:04:39,090
Yes.

76
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:47,150
Did you find it?

77
00:04:47,170 --> 00:04:47,830
No.

78
00:04:47,860 --> 00:04:48,680
I wonder whether I can...

79
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,270
Then what are you doing?

80
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:51,270
You just went up for a stroll,

81
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,560
and came down to say no?

82
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,480
Are you all putting on a show for me?

83
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,250
My son has an exam tomorrow.

84
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,800
The college entrance exam!

85
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,310
Ma'am,

86
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,000
I completely understand how you feel.

87
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,240
That's why I'd like to ask

88
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,190
whether I may speak with your son
alone for a moment.

89
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:03,720
No.

90
00:05:04,350 --> 00:05:06,300
Please don't rush to speak for him.

91
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:08,280
Or you can ask him yourself.

92
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:08,830
Okay?

93
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:09,720
No.

94
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:10,830
Why not?

95
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:12,680
You're so annoying.

96
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,940
No wonder Dad doesn't want to talk to you.

97
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:30,750
I can answer your questions,

98
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:32,040
but you must promise me

99
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:33,280
that you absolutely must not tell

100
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:35,020
what I tell you to my mom.

101
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,840
Otherwise, she'll go crazy.

102
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,240
I promise.

103
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:41,170
Go ahead.

104
00:05:43,230 --> 00:05:46,630
[Camera 05]

105
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:46,310
I had a fight with my mom
in the room yesterday.

106
00:05:46,310 --> 00:05:47,070
I was a bit annoyed,

107
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:50,190
[Camera 03]

108
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:49,250
so I wanted to be alone for a while.

109
00:05:50,270 --> 00:05:52,060
Bring up all the footage of this floor.

110
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:52,659
Okay.

111
00:05:55,659 --> 00:05:57,940
Then I went to the gym by myself.

112
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:01,240
How long were you there?

113
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:02,340
What did you do?

114
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:04,270
I didn't do anything.

115
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:05,950
I took a nap,

116
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:07,920
and hurried back
to my room when I woke up.

117
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:10,050
Did you take off your hearing aid then?

118
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,050
Do you remember?

119
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:13,780
But after that,

120
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:15,670
I never saw my hearing aid again.

121
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:19,000
Recreation Department,
Recreation Department.

122
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,680
Did you find a hearing aid?

123
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:32,890
[Camera 02]

124
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:33,800
Okay.

125
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:35,620
We can speed it up here.

126
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:36,750
Let's fast forward.

127
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:41,340
Don't worry, Ma'am.

128
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,430
We should be able to find
your lost item very soon.

129
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:45,360
Did he go somewhere
to have fun behind my back?

130
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,800
Ms. Xu, tell me,

131
00:06:46,930 --> 00:06:48,170
what did he say to you?

132
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:49,870
I'm sorry.

133
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
I can't tell you.

134
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:58,390
Why?

135
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:02,760
Why are all of you avoiding me

136
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:05,760
and telling me nothing?

137
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:09,850
I'm always thinking
about what's best for you.

138
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:14,120
Lu Xiaoyan, do you have tissues?

139
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,800
After the lady calms down,

140
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:22,240
escort her back to her hotel room to rest.

141
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:22,680
Got it?

142
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,410
Okay, got it.

143
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:25,390
Here.

144
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,850
Take this.

145
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:35,140
Recreation Department,
Recreation Department.

146
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:36,740
Did you find the hearing aid?

147
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:43,550
[Camera 02]

148
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:41,840
Pause it.

149
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:45,730
Hurry and stop the garbage truck.

150
00:07:45,730 --> 00:07:46,190
Got it.

151
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:47,460
Also, notify the lobby

152
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:49,040
and have Ms. Xu calm the guests down.

153
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:49,570
Yes, Sir.

154
00:07:51,060 --> 00:07:52,460
Hello, is this the lobby?

155
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,920
Ms. Xu, I didn't find the hearing aid.

156
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:58,040
Ms. Xu, the surveillance room
found the hearing aid.

157
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:58,790
It was mistakenly thrown

158
00:07:58,790 --> 00:08:00,040
into the garbage bag during cleaning.

159
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,390
Mr. Ji has already sent someone
to stop the garbage truck.

160
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:03,800
Okay, I'll go take a look.

161
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:10,360
Why did the garbage truck leave so fast?

162
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,270
The garbage truck left?

163
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,090
When did it leave?

164
00:08:12,090 --> 00:08:13,950
We just went out and saw it drive away.

165
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:14,960
Okay, thank you.

166
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,020
Sir, catch up with
that garbage truck ahead.

167
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:36,679
Alright.

168
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,050
It's raining.

169
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:53,380
Should I keep following that truck, Miss?

170
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:53,920
Yes.

171
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:55,480
Alright.

172
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,120
Sir.

173
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,280
Wait a minute.

174
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:35,500
Wait a minute. Sir.

175
00:09:35,530 --> 00:09:36,420
What's wrong?

176
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:38,570
I am the lobby manager of Purong Hotel.

177
00:09:39,510 --> 00:09:40,960
We have a student
taking the college entrance exam.

178
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:43,200
His hearing aid
ended up in the trash.

179
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:45,520
Could you do me a favor
and let me look for it?

180
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,650
Otherwise, it'll affect
the child's exam tomorrow.

181
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:48,450
Thank you.

182
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:51,320
Then I can only dump the garbage outside

183
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,380
for you to search, is that okay?

184
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:53,280
Yes, yes.

185
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:56,010
Wang, dump the garbage behind the truck.

186
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,030
Thank you.

187
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:07,030
[Purong Hotel]

188
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,360
Mr. Ji.

189
00:10:13,290 --> 00:10:14,600
Have the guests gone back?

190
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,220
Ms. Xu has calmed the guests down.

191
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:18,120
They are waiting in their room now.

192
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,240
Where is she now?

193
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:20,270
The garbage truck has already left.

194
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:21,600
Ms. Xu has gone after it.

195
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,000
It is raining so heavily.

196
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:24,870
She went alone?

197
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,040
Mr...

198
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:31,000
The number you dialed

199
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,060
cannot be reached.

200
00:10:32,470 --> 00:10:34,050
Please try again later.

201
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,440
The black ones are from the kitchen.

202
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:54,740
The red ones...

203
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:58,240
The red ones are from the HSKP Department.

204
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,150
The blue ones...

205
00:10:59,150 --> 00:11:00,810
The blue ones are from the gym.

206
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:05,730
Blue ones.

207
00:11:25,370 --> 00:11:26,040
Blue ones.

208
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:26,760
Blue ones.

209
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,360
Found it!

210
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,190
Found it!

211
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:46,480
Okay.

212
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:53,250
Sir.

213
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:54,450
Thank you.

214
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:55,880
I found it.

215
00:11:56,110 --> 00:11:57,130
Thank you so much.

216
00:11:58,240 --> 00:12:00,240
I made a mess of the garbage.

217
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:01,670
Let me help you clean it up.

218
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:02,360
No need.

219
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,730
It's already very late.

220
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:04,790
We will take care of it.

221
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:06,930
Hurry back and give
the thing to the student.

222
00:12:06,930 --> 00:12:07,570
Thank you.

223
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:08,740
It's nothing.

224
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,000
Xu Miyu!

225
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:54,550
I found it.

226
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:57,200
I found the student's hearing aid.

227
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,800
♪ A flicker of dim light ♪

228
00:13:00,570 --> 00:13:02,210
♪ A bowl of warm soup ♪

229
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,090
I found it!

230
00:13:04,430 --> 00:13:06,340
♪ People in the city ♪

231
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:10,100
♪ Squeezing into the hustle and bustle ♪

232
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:13,100
Are you out of your mind?

233
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:13,840
♪ The palms of time ♪

234
00:13:13,930 --> 00:13:15,740
Couldn't you ask someone else for help?

235
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:18,880
♪ Grinding away the simple days ♪

236
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,980
Can you take better care of yourself?

237
00:13:19,050 --> 00:13:20,910
Is that what you wanted to say to me?

238
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:22,410
♪ Sprinkling them into this busy world ♪

239
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:22,740
You...

240
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:24,160
My business is none of your concern!

241
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:25,450
♪ To be tasted, bit by bit ♪

242
00:13:24,630 --> 00:13:25,650
It's raining!

243
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:30,130
♪ Embracing this radiant world ♪

244
00:13:28,810 --> 00:13:29,510
Hey!

245
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:33,750
♪ Keeps the heart from fading to grey ♪

246
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:37,460
♪ Life's joy, sorrow, cold, and warmth ♪

247
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,680
♪ Intertwined within the mundane ♪

248
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:45,550
♪ Let us bravely gather up ♪

249
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:49,470
♪ The forgotten past ♪

250
00:13:50,010 --> 00:13:52,390
♪ Walking through this world ♪

251
00:13:53,810 --> 00:13:58,860
[E-bike Parking Area]

252
00:13:54,450 --> 00:13:58,330
♪ Leaving no regrets behind ♪

253
00:13:58,810 --> 00:13:59,630
Excuse me.

254
00:13:58,930 --> 00:14:00,590
[Fever Clinic]

255
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:01,520
Nurse.

256
00:14:01,630 --> 00:14:02,200
What's wrong?

257
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,000
She has a fever and fainted.

258
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:03,630
Let's find a bed first.

259
00:14:03,630 --> 00:14:04,960
You can register later.

260
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:17,430
What medicine is this?

261
00:14:17,430 --> 00:14:18,790
Why is she in so much pain?

262
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:19,750
Azithromycin.

263
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,020
It's antibacterial.

264
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:23,880
It hurts a bit when it
irritates the blood vessels.

265
00:14:26,190 --> 00:14:27,930
Is there any way to relieve it?

266
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,360
I've already slowed down the speed.

267
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,480
As her family, here's what you can do.

268
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,740
Rub it for the patient.

269
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,230
She will feel better.

270
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:37,120
Okay.

271
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:43,060
Yes.

272
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,340
Just like that.

273
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:46,270
Remember to call us when the IV runs out.

274
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:46,870
Thank you.

275
00:15:04,890 --> 00:15:07,190
♪ I know at the start of every story ♪

276
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:10,050
♪ They all feel somewhat the same ♪

277
00:15:11,940 --> 00:15:14,140
♪ Just never thought I would ♪

278
00:15:15,170 --> 00:15:17,080
♪ Fall for you so deeply ♪

279
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:21,220
♪ Why did I have to lose myself? ♪

280
00:15:21,740 --> 00:15:23,970
♪ In the virtual world ♪

281
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:30,760
♪ Unfinished dreams hurt the most ♪

282
00:15:32,180 --> 00:15:34,100
♪ Like a moth drawn to the flame ♪

283
00:15:34,580 --> 00:15:37,960
♪ Wandering aimlessly
through the night sky ♪

284
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:41,060
♪ Until I met you ♪

285
00:15:41,860 --> 00:15:44,960
♪ Like fire that finally took my life ♪

286
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:47,500
